com.github.chadwiki.elasticsearch.river.drive.connector

Class DriveConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.chadwiki.elasticsearch.river.drive.connector.DriveConnector

  • public class DriveConnector
extends Object
    This is a connector for querying and retrieving files or folders from a Google Drive. Credentials are mandatory for connecting to remote drive.
    Author:
    laurent

      • connectUserDrive

        public void connectUserDrive(String folderName)
                      throws IOException
        Actually connect to specified drive, exchanging refresh token for an up-to-date set of credentials. If folder name specified, we also retrieve subfolders to scan.
        Parameters:
        folderName - The name of the root folder to scan.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • getChanges

        public DriveChanges getChanges(Long lastChangesId)
                        throws IOException
        Query Google Drive for getting the last changes since the lastChangesId (may be null if this is the first time).
        Parameters:
        lastChangesId - The identifier of last changes to start from
        Returns:
        A bunch of changes wrapped into a DriveChanges object
        Throws:
        IOException

      • getContent

        Download Google Drive file as byte array.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        This file bytes or null if something goes wrong.

      • getDownloadUrl

        public String getDownloadUrl(com.google.api.services.drive.model.File driveFile)
        Retrieve the download url for a given drive file. Download url can vary depending on file Mime type.
        Parameters:
        driveFile - the file to get download url for.
        Returns:
        null if no suitable downlad url is found for this dile.

        Returns:
        This file mime type for indexation
